N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 22 ยง 207.36 - Failure to file timely objections

State Regulations

Whenever the time to file objections in a
proceeding has expired, objections shall not be accepted for filing unless
accompanied by a stipulation of all parties to extend the time or unless
ordered by the court. Notes
